ll manner of flattery was bestowed upon me when I founded the Sisterhood, and I hated all of it.  People asked me to do things, looked to me as an authority figure (for crying out loud, Svarinya had the GALL to ask me to marry her and Luxbane!), but all I wanted was to love them.  To the Sisters, I was &quot;Mom,&quot; and that title meant everything.  Other names, other platitudes meant nothing.<br><br>Then, I fell in love.  I didn't realize it then.  I had never felt that way toward a single person.  And who had the time!  With all the Sisters, the duties I performed, the items I sought to increase in power, the hunts and gatherings I was invited to--who had time for a relationship?  In my heart, I loved this person more than any other ... but I lied to myself.  I told myself it wasn't real ... but I found myself spending more and more time with this person, and less time with my guild.  Eventually, I made some very poor choices.  Some Sisters who had been hiding very bad attitudes came to the surface, and, for all intents and purposes, destroyed me as the leader of that guild.  There was a power struggle, and after it was all said and done ... I could no longer call the Sisterhood my home.  My family, most of them, anyway, had abandoned me.  The very family I raised for most of my time in Norrath!<br><br>But it was okay ...  I joined the Stormravens, who were a powerful guild at one time.  I wanted to see the lofty places of Norrath, the places I had yet to journey, and they could provide me that.  So I thought ... they, too, were having trouble internally.  Eventually, they also fell apart.<br><br>During my time in Stormravens, I saw my love more and more ... and ... it was beginning to dawn on me the depth of our passion.<br><br>*eyes cast down*<br><br>H- ... her name is ... Shizandra.  I ... we kept our love a secret, for fear of what people might think or say.  There is such a double-standard in Felwithe, for instance.  And I was still quite a popular figure.  The Stormravens were giving me exposure to new faces in Norrath, and I was regularly going on good camping trips.  I was learning much in the ways of magic.  But there were too many people ... and there was my image ... and ... well ... it was so complicated.<br><br>Finally ... we quit seeing each other.  I *wanted* to see her.  I wanted to feel her against me again ... I ... I am sorry.  I will spare you the details.  I ached for her.  I was lost without her.  I quit the Stormravens.  I met up with my sister Paazabel one day.  She had joined a wonderful group called the Aegis Wolves, and she said I would be welcome there.  I joined ... but ... still, I was lost.<br><br>Last week, I snapped.  I had fallen so far.  Once an easily recognized icon in Norrath ... now, no one, drowning in self-pity, sitting on the harbor walls in Firiona Vie, wishing I could slip into the sea and never resurface ... I would be forgotten.  But ... I decided that I was not going to.  I decided that appearances be damned, I was going to find Shizandra.  I was going to confess my never-ending love for her.  I was going to embrace her again, and I was going to be whole.<br><br>When I first met her, two days ago, now, she was ... evil.  I was so confused.  She wanted me to hate her.  She said the cruellest things.  She wounded me to my very foundations, and like a sick animal, I came back to be wounded again and again and again.  She had changed, and she had no love to give back to me, or so she said.<br><br>I had such hopes for our first meeting in so long ... I ... to have it so far in the opposite direction ... was excruciating.  I didn't know why she felt that way.  It wasn't the same person I fell in love with.  They had the same face, and the same name, and the same scent ... but they were *not* the same.<br><br>Yesterday ... I was going to meet her again.  The first day, I went to her broken.  The second day, I went to her in confidence.  I would not be the gibbering heap any longer.  Somewhere in this Elven frame are bones of steel, and I had started to realize ... I may actually be as strong as other people thought I was.  I faced her again, her assault unwavering, unchanged.  But she saw that this time, she wasn't getting the same reaction.  She saw that I was merely trying to understand what was happening.<br><br>Finally, I got to the root of it.  All the time we were separated ... she hated me.  I left her.  She felt abandoned by her one and only love.  Unlike me, she had ... ummm ... well, she had many relationships.  But I was the only one she ever cared for so deeply.  I was the one that took her heart when I left.  And she had nothing to give me ... because I already had taken it ... stolen it from her.<br><br>I forced her to face me ... to look me in the eye ... and tell me that she hated me.  She refused.  Finally, her anger full-throttle, she did just that.  Afterward, she was a trembling wreck ... and I knew she didn't mean it.  I saw the glimmer of love that still remained in her.  I grabbed her hair, rocked back her head, and kissed her ... and ... she kissed me back.  We wept for a time at our reunion, begging forgiveness of the other, vowing never to be parted again.<br><br>To all of you who have tried to gain my attention in the last couple of days, I appologize.  Please understand that Shizzie is, and always will be, my number one priority.  Re-gaining her took my undivided attention and complete focus ... and ... it was worth it.<br><br>I know that some of you may now see me much differently than before.  I'm not the role-model I used to be.  I am someone completely changed by this.  Not all of those changes were good, either.  My behavior may be a bit stormy, but probably no worse than any other wizard.  We aren't exactly known for our even temper.  *smirking*<br><br>If you see Aziev in game, chances are high that you will see Shizandra.  We are ... a physical couple.  If our relationship offends you, you may want to steer wide.  We refuse to hold it inside any longer, and that sometimes shocks the people around us.  *smiling, eye's gleaming*  Sometimes ... we do it for the express purpose *of* shocking them ... but I digress.<br><br>I hope that you all can accept what I have become.  If not, that is okay.  I have my home, now, even if it is not in the Wolves' den.  I know Paazabel has no plans to ever leave.  She thinks you all are just the best group anywhere, and who knows, she may just be right.  *another smirk*<br><br>(OOC -- Aziev is an emotionally charged character for me.  I have nearly 85 days played into her.  I want you to see a strange calculation: that is reaching up to 1% of my life!!!!  And if you take away the time I spend sleeping, plus the first, say, 3 years of my life, that's a pretty large chunk of my memory.  I have not been able to play, and enjoy, Aziev for a long time.  Paazabel is 34 as a direct result.  However, if Shizandra is around, Aziev will be with her.  I caution you to not take my warning lightly.  IRL, I am a hetero-sexual male.  This relationship was something the two of us wanted to pursue in game for a long time, but there were many obstacles.  I do have RL feelings for Shizandra, she is an exceptional friend, a one-of-a-kind person that I feel privilidged to have met in EQ.  The relationship between Aziev and Shizandra is very, very special, but don't assume too much about the players if you happen to see us together, okay?  Certainly, it would be an easy assumption to make.) <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub7.ezboard.com/uaziev.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aziev</A> at: 10/3/00 2:16:41 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003030><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub7.ezboard.com/usvarinya.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Svarinya</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grand Pack 