 glad to know that you support me, and that you all don't think less of me.  It does mean a great deal.<br><br>There is more to this than you all will understand.  It may be that no guild can contain us.  Perhaps Shiz will find the Wolves a welcome family.  However, right now, we sort of want to be alone together.  Our true friends are always welcome, and if *any* of you ever need a hand, Aziev is at your beck and call.  And, for the price of one wizard, chances are, you now get a pretty handy druid, too.  *smirk*<br><br>Love is where you find it.  I ... it isn't that I couldn't love a man, I don't think.  I just never thought about having *anyone.*  Shizandra came into my life and swept me away.  It was very awkward at first ... but I have learned to accept it.  Now, I can't think about having anyone *else.*  *smiling warmly*<br><br>I am not going to force anything to happen.  The purpose of a journey is not to arrive.  Whatever happens over the next few days will probably shape the future for me for quite some time.  No matter what happens, know that I love you all a great deal.<br><br>Az <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003030><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub7.ezboard.com/urematus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rematus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elder</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(10/3/00 1:33:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub7.ezboard.com/faegiswolvestunarepack.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=260.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: In Character, Out of Character</span><hr size=1> Aviez<br><br>Know that wherever your ship takes you in the travels of the world, I for one will be there as a friend and a brother.  If you so happen to leave our family....well you cannot really leave, maybe just assume a different name <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/e